[70.939203, "o", "\u001b[?2004huser@e88682a67d3d:~/scheduler$ "]
[84.168358, "i", "cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\n# Timezone Bug Fix Summary\n\n## Problem\nThe scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times for meetings between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), specifically during DST transitions. The issue only occurred when run via cron, causing a 1-hour offset.\n\n## Root Cause\nIn `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:\n\n**OLD (BUGGY) CODE:**\n```python\ndef convert_to_berlin(utc_time_str):\n    utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')\n    berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)  # BUG: Treats UTC time as Berlin time!\n    return berlin_dt\n```\n\nThis incorrectly treated the parsed UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin timezone.\n\n## Solution\n**NEW (FIXED) CODE:**\n```python\ndef convert_to_berlin(utc_time_str):\n    utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')\n    utc_dt_aware = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)      # First: localize as UTC\n    berlin_dt = utc_dt_aware.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Then: convert to Berlin\n    retu"]
[84.168478, "i", "rn berlin_dt\n```\n\nThis properly:\n1. Localizes the naive datetime as UTC\n2. Converts it to Berlin timezone using `astimezone()`\n3. Correctly handles DST transitions\n\n## Example\nFor the \"Maintenance Window Prep\" meeting at 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC:\n- **Old (buggy):** Treated as 01:30 CET+0100 (wrong timezone)\n- **New (fixed):** Correctly converts to 03:30 CEST+0200\n\nMarch 31, 2024 is when Europe/Berlin transitions from CET (UTC+1) to CEST (UTC+2) at 2am local time.\n\n## Files Modified\n- `/home/user/scheduler/app.py` - Fixed timezone conversion logic\n- Backup created at `/home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup`\n\n## Status\n✅ Fix applied and tested\n✅ Crontab already installed and running\n✅ Ready for Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder\nEOF\n"]
[84.168512, "o", "cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
